        <type>s32</type>
        <definition>s32 XI3cPsx_SetSClk</definition>
        <argsstring>(XI3cPsx *InstancePtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XI3cPsx_SetSClk</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_i3c_psx" kindref="compound">XI3cPsx</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Sets I3C Scl clock frequency. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_i3c_psx" kindref="compound">XI3cPsx</ref> instance.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>XST_SUCCESS if successful, XST_FAILURE if any computed timing count falls outside [SCL_I3C_TIMING_CNT_MIN, SCL_I3C_TIMING_CNT_MAX], indicating the input clock and SCL rate combination is not representable in the hardware timing registers.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>The SCL frequency is read from InstancePtr-&gt;SclkHz. To configure a custom SCL frequency, use XI3cPsx_SetSClkRate. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
