        <briefdescription>
<para>Sets a custom I3C SCL clock frequency by updating the instance SCL rate and configuring the hardware registers accordingly. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_i3c_psx" kindref="compound">XI3cPsx</ref> instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>SclkHz</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the desired SCL clock frequency in Hz.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>XST_SUCCESS if successful, XST_FAILURE if the requested SCL rate cannot be represented in the hardware timing registers for the given input clock.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This updates InstancePtr-&gt;SclkHz and programs the hardware. For default SCL rate set during initialization, use XI3cPsx_SetSClk instead. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
